Average Statistics for Half-Elves<br>
<br>
Height: males about 4'8"-5'10'<br>
        females about 4'6"-5'8"<br>
<br>
Hair: Ranging in colors usally tending towards lighter colors, but a few with<br>
      black hair have been seen. Half-elves also tend to have little to no<br>
      facial hair<br>
<br>
Eyes: Primarily Blue, Green or (rarely) Gray iris. A few Half-Elves also have<br>
      the almond shaped eyes of the elves.<br>
<br>
Affiliation: light or dark based on alignment / how you role-play it.<br>
<br>
Appearance: Half-elves always appear more human than elven or vyan.  Though<br>
neither as tall nor as muscular as humans, half-elves have sturdy frames.<br>
Their hair, skin and eyes comes in a variety of different shades, depending<br>
upon the dominant features of their parents.  A half-elf has slightly<br>
less pronounced pointed ears but can manage a full beard, unlike those of<br>
elven blood.  The skin tones of most half-elves is a slightly golden color,<br>
though this can vary depending upon their human blood.<br>
<br>
Optional Advice on Role Playing an Half-Elf<br>
<br>
Half-Elves are as the name implies the offspring of a human and an elf or vyan.<br>
As such they are shunned by all most all other races. They are nomadic in<br>
nature rarely staying in one town long. Many Half-Elves have been killed by<br>
other races who fear them saying they are an abomination as mixed breeds. <br>
Those who make it past adolsence have had to learned to be independant,<br>
trusting no one in order to survive.<br>
